Package model

Class Appointment

Object
Appointment
public class Appointment extends Object
Represents an appointment scheduled between a patient and a doctor. Each appointment has a unique ID, status, date, time slot, and may include an outcome.
Since:
2024-10-27
Version:
4.6
Author:
Chew En Zee

  • Constructor Details

    • Appointment

      public Appointment(String date, int timeSlot, Patient patient, Doctor doctor)
      Constructs a new Appointment with the specified date, time slot, patient, and doctor. The appointment is initialized with a status of PENDING and a unique appointment ID.
      Parameters:
      date - the date of the appointment
      timeSlot - the time slot of the appointment
      patient - the patient involved in the appointment
      doctor - the doctor involved in the appointment

    • Appointment

      public Appointment(String appointmentID, Doctor doctor, AppointmentStatus appointmentStatus, Patient patient, String date, int timeSlot)
      Constructs an Appointment with the specified ID, doctor, status, patient, date, and time slot. This constructor is useful for initializing appointments with known IDs and statuses.
      Parameters:
      appointmentID - the unique ID of the appointment
      doctor - the doctor involved in the appointment
      appointmentStatus - the current status of the appointment
      patient - the patient involved in the appointment
      date - the date of the appointment
      timeSlot - the time slot of the appointment
